    description: 'Bhutanese cuisine is fiery, rustic, and deeply tied to high-altitude farming life. Chilies are not a spice but a vegetable — eaten raw, dried, and cooked in large quantities. Red rice, buckwheat, and yak meat sustain communities above 3,000 meters.',
