    funFact: 'Traditional Qatari gahwa (Arabic coffee) is always served unsweetened, cardamom-spiced, and in a small handleless cup (finjan). It is always accompanied by dates — the combination is so embedded in Qatari culture that refusing it is considered mildly impolite.',
