    funFact: 'Sweden\'s crayfish season (kräftskiva) in August is one of Scandinavia\'s greatest food rituals — parties gather under paper lanterns, wear bibs, and eat crayfish with dill schnapps and singing. The tradition dates to 17th-century aristocratic dining.',
