    funFact: 'Romania is the world\'s sixth-largest plum producer, and the country distills much of it into țuică — a potent plum brandy of 50–60% alcohol. Virtually every Romanian village produces its own țuică in copper pot stills, and it is traditionally offered to every arriving guest.',
