    funFact: 'Šljivovica (Serbian plum brandy) is so intertwined with Serbian culture that it has Protected Geographical Indication status. Serbia produces around 3 million hectoliters of plum brandy annually and it is customary to offer rakija at every social occasion, from christenings to funerals.',
