    description: 'Lithuanian cuisine is robust Baltic cooking built on rye, potatoes, pork, and dairy — sustaining communities through long, cold winters. Cepelinai (massive potato dumplings shaped like zeppelins) and šaltibarščiai (cold beet soup) are the country\'s most distinctive dishes.',
