    description: 'Burkinabe cuisine is shaped by the Sahel\'s challenging climate — drought-resistant millet and sorghum are the caloric foundation; leafy sauces made from baobab leaves or moringa add nutrition. Tô (millet porridge) is the national staple; the cuisine is honest and deeply communal.',
