    funFact: 'Guinea is home to the Fula (Fulani) people — one of West Africa\'s great cattle-herding groups — who have contributed a rich dairy tradition to Guinean cuisine. Fula milk and butter are staples in northern Guinea and traded across the Sahel region.',
