    funFact: 'Namibia has the highest concentration of cheetahs in the world, and Namibian game farms now raise oryx, kudu, and springbok for meat that is exported to European luxury food markets. Namibian game meat is farmed in conditions so wild it is essentially free-range hunting by cattle standards.',
