    funFact: 'Chile is the world\'s largest producer of lithium (used in batteries), copper, and lapis lazuli — but culinarily its most remarkable product is its extraordinary variety of native potato. Chile\'s southern Chiloé island has over 200 endemic potato varieties, the most diverse potato biodiversity in the world outside Peru.',
