    description: 'Cuban cuisine is a creole synthesis of Spanish, African, and Caribbean influences — developed by African slaves who fused their Yoruba, Congo, and Mandinka food traditions with Spanish colonial cooking. Ropa vieja (shredded beef stew), black beans, and rice form the Cuban national table.',
