    funFact: 'Cuba\'s food rationing system (libreta) has been in place since 1962 — one of the longest-running food rationing programs in history. Despite shortages, Cuban families have maintained a rich culinary culture, and Cuban exiles have carried their food traditions to Miami, creating one of America\'s most vibrant immigrant food scenes.',
