    funFact: 'Ecuador is the world\'s largest exporter of bananas — supplying around 25% of global banana trade. The word "Ecuador" means equator in Spanish, and the country\'s equatorial climate makes it the perfect environment for growing the Cavendish banana that dominates world markets.',
