    funFact: 'Costa Rica is one of the world\'s five "Blue Zones" — regions where people consistently live past 100. The Nicoya Peninsula\'s diet of beans, corn tortillas, squash, and tropical fruits, combined with strong social bonds and low stress, has produced one of the world\'s most studied longevity populations.',
